pull_request.title: Add sanitizer builds
pull_request.body: A very simple `--with-sanitizer` to enable ASAN and UBSAN. This will produce a couple errors that will need to get fixed before this should be enabled on CI. Note that this should always go along with  `CC=clang`.

pull_request.title: Clean up heap on success
pull_request.body: Using `goto` isn't great but at least you won't leak this way.

pull_request.title: Use OpenSSL's EVP_MD_CTX_new and _free
pull_request.body:
Fixes #565.

Does so by requiring OpenSSL version 1.1.0 or higher.  But one of our target platforms (Ubuntu Xenial 16.04) only comes with OpenSSL 1.0.2.  So what should we do?  Require users on that platform to build OpenSSL 1.0.2 (and update our Docker images accordingly)?  Or remove that as a target platform?  Thoughts, @baentsch and @xvzcf?
